title: Man to Men [1948 - Switzerland] Nobel Peace Prize + Red Cross
description: Man to Men [1948 - France, Switzerland] D'homme à hommes Biography / Drama http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0125054/ Depicts Henri Dunant and the beginning of the Red Cross. Dunant, a Swiss businessman and social activist, was the founder of the Red Cross and the first recipient of the Nobel Peace Prize. The 1864 Geneva Convention was based on Dunant's ideas.
